    "originContent": "## What Makes This Different",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 118,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": "### Aplicación, No Sugerencias"
  },
  {
    "row": 119,
    "rowsha": "GpWKZ64MvYWD0Eb6O3NDyFV0Uh4CRye4+3Xk6iLIibI=",
    "originContent": "### Enforcement, Not Suggestions",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 120,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": "13 hooks en 5 eventos del ciclo de vida. No advierten — bloquean. El orquestador no puede editar código en main. Los supervisores no pueden saltarse beads. Las épicas no pueden cerrarse con hijos abiertos. `git commit --no-verify` está bloqueado — los hooks pre-commit siempre se ejecutan."
  },
  {
    "row": 121,
    "rowsha": "90f20CcSXhNw+QVU+sXAz7x35BJbFHyMCpuEQzdwNcw=",
    "originContent": "13 hooks across 5 lifecycle events. They don't warn — they block. The orchestrator can't edit code on main. Supervisors can't skip beads. Epics can't close with open children. `git commit --no-verify` is blocked — pre-commit hooks always run.",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 122,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": "### Investigación Primero, Restricciones Como Guía"
  },
  {
    "row": 123,
    "rowsha": "DC43t0Pf/6MswN/5WVo6hzzZTNyDyjovJ3b98fd49EE=",
    "originContent": "### Investigation-First, Constraint-Driven",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 124,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": "El orquestador debe leer el archivo fuente real antes de delegar — no adivina. Las restricciones (\"nunca despachar sin leer la fuente\") superan las instrucciones (\"recuerda investigar\"), inspirado por la investigación multi-agente de [Cursor](https://cursor.com/blog/self-driving-codebases). El orquestador también mantiene memoria persistente entre sesiones."
  },
  {
    "row": 125,
    "rowsha": "CH926wMlqziMfdh5KE/ejq4ukGko9eC9o+ImJfPmLyU=",
    "originContent": "The orchestrator must read the actual source file before delegating — no guessing. Constraints (\"never dispatch without reading the source\") outperform instructions (\"remember to investigate\"), inspired by [Cursor's multi-agent research](https://cursor.com/blog/self-driving-codebases). The orchestrator also maintains persistent memory across sessions.",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 126,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": "### Documentación Que Se Escribe Sola"
  },
  {
    "row": 127,
    "rowsha": "7GpI8gLKBfekiemty0rGCUiPQr8sFwRCOt5iu/MZJa8=",
    "originContent": "### Documentation That Writes Itself",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
    "row": 128,
    "rowsha": "47DEQpj8HBSa+/TImW+5JCeuQeRkm5NMpJWZG3hSuFU=",
    "originContent": "",
    "translatedContent": "Cada prompt de despacho del supervisor se captura automáticamente como comentario bead. Los agentes registran voluntariamente convenciones y advertencias en una base de conocimiento persistente. Al iniciar la sesión, se muestra conocimiento reciente para que los agentes no vuelvan a investigar problemas ya resueltos."
  },
  {
    "row": 129,
    "rowsha": "nreHiN0hJma4sWt6baNLqdMz5UeNi60zwoNEOADSjow=",
    "originContent": "Every supervisor dispatch prompt is automatically captured as a bead comment. Agents voluntarily log conventions and gotchas into a persistent knowledge base. Session start surfaces recent knowledge so agents don't re-investigate solved problems.",
    "translatedContent": ""
  },
  {
